WRITING.TEXT: Drilling a drainage hole is insanely easy. I've done it many times

Drill it under water or keep it wet so it doesn't overheat and crack. I drill holes in sea glass with the same drill bits and learned the hard way the first couple times until I read up on it. I don't know if it's just the drill bits I use (They are just drillbits for drilling into tile that I bought at Lowes) but that's the only precaution I would take. Maybe just try it on a cheap pot that you don't care about first to test the waters. P.S. after doing it probably 20+ times I still get nervous ;D
